data.title: Emmy Rossum Biography
data.meta_description: Read all about Emmy Rossum with TV Guide's exclusive biography including their list of awards, celeb facts and more at TV Guide.
data.text:
Fast Facts

Was named for her maternal grandfather Began her career at age 7 in the children's choir of the Metropolitan Opera, earning $5 a day

Over five seasons at the Met, she appeared in 20 productions and sang in five languages

Played Audrey Hepburn as a teen in a 2000 TV-biopic

Earned an Independent Spirit Award nomination in the category of Best Debut Performance for the 2001 film Songcatcher

Took cooking classes at Le Cordon Bleu in London

Won a Young Artist Award for Best Performance in a Feature Film for 2004's The Phantom of the Opera

Released her debut album, Inside Out, in 2007, plus a three-song Christmas EP titled Carol of the Bells

Her second album, 2013's Sentimental Journey, which featured cover songs from the 1920s to '60s
